<DOCNO> AP901231-0003 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
in this country there arent 
enough white people to handle all the managerial positions 
johann haasbroek said you have to use people of other 
cultures 
driving a pickup over bumpy trails cut through maize and wheat 
fields northwest of johannesburg the 57yearold farmer explained 
why he began promoting black workers more than a decade ago 
such radical action was considered suicidal in the rightwing 
world of south african farming but it worked for haasbroek who 
runs a successful family farm and is setting up another for his 
son 
he employs five whites and about 60 or 70 fulltime blacks 
at the main farm some of the black workers hire seasonal work 
crews and manage specific areas of the operation 
when i was young youd very seldom get a black man who wanted 
to be a foreman haasbroek said there was a lot of 
superstition more than now among the blacks they thought 
something would happen to them 
then need and ambition combined and about 12 years ago one 
of my black workers said he was willing to train as a foreman he 
said when pressed the farmer acknowledged encouraging the man 
i said you know it would be much easier if i could have one 
of you guys as foreman it would take a lot of responsibility off 
my hands he recalled 
new responsibilities led to new commitment on both sides 
haasbroek said workers displayed a better attitude he said and 
he let them open a school for their children on the farm 
some of the workers attended courses on farm management at 
government training centers at their employers expense 
they give the basics of how it should be done not only seen 
from a job point of view but communication among themselves and 
other things he said of the training centers 
the result of it all in haasbroeks view is a stable group of 
workers who take pride in the farm 
id never say it was expressed in words but in their way of 
doing things taking responsibility and doing it for themselves 
theyre all very proud of the farm he said 
for instance we have two soccer teams they always want to 
win theyre very proud of the team 
people are like trees haasbroek said with some growing taller 
and straighter than others 
the big thing is to be able to identify the bloke who can do 
it he said theres a lot of potential in these people waiting 
to be developed 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

