lifethreatening health problems associated with low birthweight 
babies and her parents were not sure they would ever be able to 
bring her home 
laura was put in a neonatal intensive care unit and given a 
hormone to help her lungs develop the march of dimes said it led 
the development of the units for highrisk infants and its 
researchers have studied the effects of the type of hormone laura 
was given 
laura overcame the odds 
the miracle of laura is not just the fact that she lived the 
miracle is that she has virtually no problems as a result of her 
prematurity mrs krumwiede said 
