<TEXT>
communistrun businesses and currency speculators 
in berlin cost the government 666 million by manipulating aspects 
of german unification an official said monday 
berlin justice sen jutta limbach said officials have identified 
54 specific cases where people managed to make vast amounts of 
money off the economic merger of the german nations 
but she said it will take at least six months to sift through 
evidence needed to bring criminal charges 
west germanys powerful currency replaced east germanys 
nonconvertible communist currency on july 1 and the two nations 
united on oct 3 
even though the communist currency was considered worthless 
outside the east bloc it was exchanged for the western mark at a 
11 rate for small personal bank accounts and at a 21 rate for 
corporate and large accounts 
limbach said her office has turned up about 1 billion marks or 
666 million in economic damage caused primarily by former 
communistrun businesses that doctored their financial records 
all of the suspected fraud took place in former east berlin she 
said and 700 million marks or 466 million in fraud was blamed 
on businesses that had soviet rubles in their bank accounts 
the government allowed east german businesses to convert rubles 
in their bank accounts to west german marks at a 21 rate for 
recent transactions even though the ruble was worth only a 
fraction of that 
officials have charged that many businesses altered their 
records to make it look like older transactions took place 
recently allowing the enterprises to convert large amounts of 
rubles in their accounts at the 21 rate 
she said other losses were caused by currency speculation and 
illegal property sales 
officials have said that economic crimes related to german 
unification probably will reach billions of marks nationwide 
</TEXT>
