<TEXT>
george allen who transformed 
two professional football teams from losers to winners then came 
out of a fiveyear retirement to take over a struggling 
smallcollege team died monday he was 72 
allen who coached the los angeles rams and washington redskins 
of the nfl also served as chairman of the presidents council on 
physical fitness from 1981 going on television to exhort americans 
to shape up 
he died at his home here of natural causes said his son greg 
he is survived by his wife etty a daughter and three sons 
allen was alone at home when his wife returned in the early 
afternoon and found him dead in the kitchen said mike tracy of the 
palos verdes estates police department she had last seen him alive 
at 1030 am 
allen who also coached two teams with the shortlived usfl in 
the early 1980s had ended a fiveyear retirement to coach at long 
beach state in december 1989 he said at the time he missed the 
challenge 
allen ranks as the winningest coach in team history for both the 
rams and the redskins and had the thirdbest winning percentage of 
712 among nfl coaches with 100 or more victories he was 49174 
or 742 with los angeles from 1966 to 1970 and 67301 or 691 
with washington from 1971 to 1977 
although he had excellent records in the pros he never was able 
to produce a national football league champion the closest he came 
was with the redskins in the 1972 season when they lost 147 to 
the miami dolphins in the seventh super bowl 
allen said his 65 winning season at long beach state this year 
was the most rewarding of his entire career the team scored 48 
the previous season 
in an interview last thursday allen said his health had 
suffered since his players drenched him with icewater to celebrate 
a seasonending victory over nevadalas vegas we couldnt afford 
gatorade he said smiling 
however allen had been showing up recently at the practices of 
the iowa hawkeyes who were holding drills at long beach state in 
preparation for tuesdays rose bowl game against washington he was 
at practice sunday and appeared fit and animated 
allens celebrated coaching career which covered four decades 
began in 1948 at morningside college in sioux city iowa in his 
first year the team had a 36 record 
it was one of only three times he had a losing record the other 
two coming at whittier college in 1951 and 1954 
he took over the struggling los angeles rams in 1966 and led the 
team to a 86 record their first winning season in eight years 
the next year the rams finished first in the division with an 
1112 record allens best singleseason mark 
allen was known for wild spending to build a winner and trading 
draft choices for such veterans as defensive linemen diron talbert 
ron mcdole and richie petitbon earning the redskins the nickname 
the over the hill gang 
the nine games he won in his first season were the most 
washington had managed in 29 years 
his basic philosophy was us against them said petitbon who 
played for allen with the chicago bears rams and redskins and 
became his assistant in washington he made enemies of everyone 
the media other teams and it was effective he was a great 
motivator the players loved him 
redskins owner jack kent cooke said allen was a trojan for 
work and for winning he was one of the indestructibles 
though the redskins kept winning allen was fired after the 1977 
season the late edward bennett williams who owned the team at 
that time said george was given an unlimited budget and 
exceeded it 
allen landed back in los angeles but the rams fired him just 
two games into the 1978 exhibition schedule 
allen also had two winning seasons in the nowdefunct united 
states football league he coached the arizona wranglers in 1984 
where he was 108 and the chicago blitz in 1983 leading them to a 
126 mark 
i talked to coach allen a few weeks ago and he was just so 
excited about the winning season he had at long beach state said 
houston oilers coach jack pardee who played under allen as a 
linebacker with the washington redskins 
coach allen always thrived on building something out of very 
little pardee said and he was very excited about the 
continuing challenge that he had at long beach 
george really did turn things around for the rams and got us 
on a winning track said hall of fame defensive lineman merlin 
olsen who played under allen he always carried such great 
enthusiasm with him and was one of the consummate motivators 
an advocate of physical fitness who competed in marathons 
bikeathons and triathlons allen founded the national fitness 
foundation in 1952 a member of the presidents council on physical 
fitness for several years he was named chairman by president 
reagan in 1981 
allen wrote 11 books on football one of which was the first 
encyclopedia of football drills 
allens friends in washington included president nixon he once 
used a play nixon diagrammed for a playoff game against the san 
francisco 49ers the reverse to wide receiver roy jefferson went 
for a loss 
