<TEXT>
military ruler lt gen omar hassan 
elbashir said monday he was putting islamic law into effect at 
once in all parts of sudan except the south dominated by 
christians and animists 
elbashir said the 1400year old islamic sharia law would cover 
only administrative and civil cases and that rules for criminal 
cases would await application of a federal system here he did not 
specify when that would be 
he said he was committing himself personally to drafting a 
decisive timetable and administrative measures necessary for 
realization of sharia law 
elbashir said sharia law would also cover banking and financial 
dealings abolishing interest payment it was not immediately clear 
how that would affect international transactions with this 
northcentral african nation and its population of about 25 
million 
elbashir spoke on the occasion of the 35th anniversary of 
sudans independence from joint britishegyptian rule 
thenpresident gaafar nimeiri introduced islamic law in 1983 
but it was suspended after nimeiris overthrow in 1985 elbashir 
deposed former prime minister sadek elmahdi in june 1989 
nimeiris introduction of the sharia was a factor in sudans 
being plunged into civil war renegade col john garang and his 
sudan peoples liberation army in 1983 took up arms in the south 
against the muslimdominated government 
many sentences were passed and implemented under sharia law 
including cutting off hands for theft flogging and public disgrace 
for adultery 
scrapping sharia law has been a rebel condition for ending the 
war 
mondays announcement was broadcast live on television which 
showed hundreds of people cheering elbashir around the 
presidential palace in the capital khartoum while shouting we 
will protect islam with our blood 
referring to southern sudan elbashir said the present legal 
system will remain unchanged until the establishement of new 
legislative bodies with power to decide the appropriate legal 
system befitting the south 
he told a jubilant crowd it became imperative and inevitable 
that we should immediately apply the sharia aw without delay or 
procrastination in response to the will of allah and the popular 
demand 
