<TEXT>
a summary of developments in the news industry for the week of 
dec 2431 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the publics attention was riveted to the 
persian gulf crisis more closely than to any other news story in 
1990 a year in which international events overshadowed domestic 
news 
the times mirror center for the people and the press found that 
twothirds of the public closely followed stories about the iraqi 
invasion of kuwait and the deployment of american forces to the 
region 
by comparison the historic fall of communism in almost all of 
eastern europe and the economic and political turmoil in the soviet 
union failed to interest most americans at no point did more than 
30 percent of americans closely follow these events according to 
the centers monthly surveys 
the most closely followed domestic news story also had a link to 
the mideast crisis sixtytwo percent of those surveyed said they 
regularly read stories about soaring gasoline prices in august and 
september 
by comparison reports in november about the declining economy 
attracted only 39 percent of the readers on a regular basis 
stories leading up to and including the november general election 
caught the regular attention of only 38 percent as did stories 
last january about the war against drugs 
only one other news event involving us soldiers fighting 
abroad caught the close attention of more than a majority of 
americans sixty percent of americans regularly read stories about 
the us invasion of panama although us forces invaded panama on 
dec 20 1989 their presence in the country and numerous news 
stories continued into this year 
the centers figures are based on monthly telephone surveys of 
1200 adults nationwide 
public interest in some issues shifted significantly during the 
year 
last spring only 18 percent of the public paid close attention 
to stories about the first signs of economic problems the 
percentage had increased to 29 percent by september and it was 39 
percent in november 
there was only scant attention to the nations budget deficit 
last spring when rep dan rostenkowski dill proposed a deficit 
reduction plan during the summer as congress debated a budget 
package 18 percent of the readers were following the issue 
closely but public attention increased to 34 percent by the fall 
amid threats to shut down the federal government 
interest in news concerning president bush also fluctuated 
when bush attended the drug summit in columbia last february 
only 22 percent of the public paid close attention to stories about 
the visit criticism of the president on his changing position on 
taxes and his persian gulf policy caught the close attention of 
slightly less than a third of the public 
by contrast three out of four people read last march about 
bushs distaste for broccoli 
sensational crimes and trials drew substantial public interest 
news about the serial killings in gainesville fla attracted 
more public attention 36 percent than any other crime story 
during the year twentyeight percent of the readers followed the 
drug arrest of mayor marion barry of washington dc but interest 
waned only 16 percent paid close attention to stories about 
barrys conviction on some of the charges 
some stories attracted less public interest than expected 
despite the extensive coverage of the nomination of david souter 
to the us supreme court only about 15 percent followed the event 
closely 
and more than half of the people surveyed said they strongly 
felt too much was written about the marital breakup of donald and 
ivana trump twelve percent of the public said they closely 
followed the affair 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
iraqs invasion of kuwait and the heartstopping 
standoff that ensued in the persian gulf was by far the top news 
story of 1990 according to an ap poll of newpaper editors and 
broadcast news directors 
in the balloting by 327 news people the gulf crisis finished 
well ahead of the story that placed second the reunification of 
germany 
here are the top 10 stories with vote totals based on 10 points 
for an editors no 1 choice down to one for the no 10 pick 
1 iraq invades kuwait making hostages of thousands of 
