figures said dec 27 that he knew who sent him the material and 
promised the source anonymity 
the us attorneys office wants to recover the documents from 
two newspapers and three television stations so investigators can 
trace the leak 
initially six news outlets that received the documents were 
subpoenaed to give them to a federal grand jury the tribunereview 
of greensburg relinquished the documents 
lawyers for the pittsburgh press the pittsburgh postgazette 
and television stations kdka and wpxi filed motions seeking to 
quash the subpoenas wtaetv also received the documents but did 
not join in the motions 
