received the documents in the mail several weeks before other news 
organizations did bucsko said he knew the source and had promised 
not to reveal the identity 
assistant us attorney linda l kelly didnt ask bucsko to name 
the source in court 
attorneys for the news organizations argued that relinquishing 
the documents could ultimately identify the source whether 
reporters know the source or not 
us district judge donald j lee took the matter under 
advisement 
the government claims the documents known as fbi 302 reports 
