he has no job and no money for rent but 
carpenter reuben soto still believes the northwests economy is 
tops in the nation 
trouble is hes right 
in the late 1980s the northwest became the jewel of the us 
economy sparkling atop charts of economic growth and livability 
the region still outshines the gloomy national economy but thats 
not saying much as reuben soto discovered firsthand the great 
northwest boom is fading 
he came from virginia last summer a 35yearold bachelor 
looking for work and a fresh start in life hed heard times were 
good around seattle and sure enough things started out well soto 
