editors note some hollywood stars have become almost as 
wellknown for the causes they support as for the parts they play 
jane fonda charlton heston and edward asner come immediately to 
mind while those three may represent an older generation show 
business today is not without its activists concerned about such 
issues as the environment energy abortion and the homeless 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
academy awards night typically finds 
hollywood in a selfindulgent mood the stars lavishing themselves 
with fine clothes finer praise and the finest food 
some but not all 
as the guests preened for last years oscar presentations 
actors ron silver susan sarandon alec baldwin christopher reeve 
and jennifer beales had more serious business at hand 
they are members of an advocacy group called the creative 
coalition and spent all day with new york gov mario cuomo and 
state legislators pushing environmental legislation and sounding 
the alarm of global warming 
in addition to the creative coalition a growing group of 
entertainment figures are cashiering their fame for good works 
performing at benefits and actually embracing causes as if their 
careers and sometimes their lives depended on it 
while the stereotype of the ineffectual celebrity dogooder 
persists these performers writers directors and executives 
endeavor to be both dedicated and knowledgeable 
this is five days a week of two people working regular 
hours says robert foxworth the former falcon crest star who 
along with assistant bobbi murray produces a weekly issueoriented 
radio show with his own money 
ed begley jr st elsewhere is one of hollywoods most 
dedicated activists frequently sacrificing his time and creature 
comforts for energy conservation 
living in a home illuminated by lowenergy 15watt light bulbs 
and commuting to work by bus bicycle or electric car begleys 
lifestyle strives to be as environmentally conscientious as 
possible 
in november begley was named chairman of an advisory committee 
to the southern california rapid transit district which runs the 
citys bus system and is building a massive subway network 
mr begleys commitment to public transit as well as his 
involvement in environmental issues will provide strong 
leadership says rtd board president nick patsaouras 
most actors and actresses say when it comes to choosing between 
their careers and their causes employment comes first without 
work these activists have neither a platform nor money to pledge 
what separates real activists from fairweather warriors is the 
level of sacrifice 
foxworths american dialogues program for example is 
supported entirely by foxworths earnings and falcon crest 
savings 
the 5yearold show heard in 75 cities has foxworth 
interviewing experts in a spectrum of social issues from the war 
on drugs to campaign finances to central american politics 
its always been a frustration to some extent that the work in 
film television and theater hasnt been able to be more focused on 
issues says foxworth sitting in a recording studio built over 
his garage we have our podium our pedestal is to some extent 
our career it provides some access to people 
silver who was one of the founders of the nonpartisan creative 
coalition says entertainers have a duty to charity 
i think theres almost an obligation says silver the 
costar of the film reversal of fortune many of us are very 
well compensated for work which a lot of people would love to do 
and we also have a lot of leisure time in between jobs 
the more visible members of our group use their access and 
utilize their attentiongetting abilities to bring a lot of issues 
to the publics attention silver says 
the 250 show business professionals in the new yorkbased group 
lobby local and national politicians about issues such as the 
environment freedom of expression abortion rights and the 
homeless 
they say that hollywood is sex without substance and 
washington politics is substance without sex so maybe the marriage 
of the two is mutually intriguing silver says 
there are more than a few celebrities who have become almost as 
wellknown for the causes they support as for the parts they play 
jane fondas acting career has been tinged by her activism 
during the vietnam war when she appeared on radio hanoi and begged 
american soldiers to stop bombing to some she is as much hanoi 
jane as she is the star of 1981s on golden pond or 1989s 
stanley and iris 
during filming of the latter in 1988 a waterbury conn 
veterans helped circulate bumper stickers that read im not 
fonda hanoi jane 
im a good scapegoat miss fonda said in an interview not 
long ago i can be painted into an image which causes a lot of 
hostility i may not be that person but thats irrelevant 
charlton heston ben hur donates time to the national rifle 
association and lobbies against government funding for explicit 
art mike farrell mash is recognized as one of the 
nation strongest voices for civil rights singer jackson browne 
whose concerts are loaded with plugs for causes said that some 
fans have taken to yelling just sing 
