<TEXT>
vietnam is often seen in retrospect through the 
eyes of americans rarely is it viewed from the vietnamese 
perspective 
but an old american foe former infantryman nguyen ngoc hung 
gave some rare glimpses from the north vietnamese side during a 
recent tour of the united states 
on victory the vietnamese were determined to carry it to the 
end we didnt aim to defeat the americans we fought to drive 
the americans home and in 1973 the americans had to withdraw 
because of the killings but also it was due to the antiwar 
movement in the united states so we didnt actually defeat the 
americans we drove them away 
on the body count in america whenever they fought a battle 
they say ok one american 20 vietnamese killed they won the 
battle they won many battles in vietnam but what was the point 
here it is our country if we lost the war we have no other place 
to go we understood how barbarous the french colonialist system 
was and for many vietnamese we didnt see any difference between 
the war against the french colonialists and the war against the 
americans 
on antiwar demonstrations in the united states the war is 
actually fought not only in vietnam but also in the united states 
it would have been very difficult for the vietnamese to end this 
war without the antiwar movement in the united states because i 
know how strong and how powerful the air force and artillery 
support of the american army and navy were during the war 
comparing the americans to their southern vietnamese allies 
it was difficult to fight against the americans it was not 
difficult to fight the southern vietnamese army because most of 
the soldiers didnt know why they had to fight they were drafted 
from schools and from families and nobody wanted to go to war most 
of the american veterans told me the same story they didnt like 
the southern vietnamese soldiers and they didnt trust them 
</TEXT>
