<TEXT>
costumes are often forgotten once films are 
over but not when glenn close is around her closet includes suits 
from jagged edge an overcoat from fatal attraction and the 
marquise de merteuils lowcut gownsfrom dangerous liasions 
she takes good care of those clothes she never knows when 
theyll be needed recently for example the fashion institute of 
technology asked her to donate her wardrobe from reversal of 
fortune for an exhibit on fashion in film close was able to 
oblige 
her costumes are also a reminder of a daring complicated life 
on screen a career spent in coats of many colors from pure white 
in the natural to shining black in fatal attraction 
those characters all stay with me in some way said close 
dressed for a recent interview in a mocha brown suede jacket and 
tan pants an appropriate outfit for a woman who grew up on a 
500acre estate in greenwich conn 
you have to love your character even alex forrest of fatal 
attraction who was a very haunting character you become 
intimate you gain an understanding of their behavior and i usually 
emphasize deeply with them 
as the reserved unhappy sunny von bulow of reversal of 
fortune she favored a sweater outfit with a single strand of 
pearls she wore gowns and long earrings for her new film 
hamlet portraying queen gertrude in the latest version of 
shakespeares classic tragedy 
hamlet stars mel gibson as the danish prince incapable of 
making up his mind and also features alan bates ian holm paul 
scofield and helena bonham carter 
close a veteran stage actress was not in awe of portraying 
gertrude she went about it like any other part reading the play 
several times watching other films of hamlet and taking a 
personal approach to analyzing her character 
i just decided she was married very young and married a man 
much older than her for political reasons said close a 
fivetime academy award nominee 
all the descriptions of her come across as a very tactile 
very sensual woman the ghosts and the king and hamlet revolved 
around her theres something in that woman thats dazzling 
necessary sensual selfish 
she was born in 1947 in greenwich which her ancestors helped 
found in the late 17th century growing up close never dressed 
like a queen but remembers years spent in the country playing 
makebelieve in a number of roles a bride a cowboy an orphan a 
woman dying of cancer 
helping were her two grandmothers one had wanted to be a 
singer the other an actress they were perfect coaches exposing 
her to opera and ballet even offering tricks for improving the 
memory she also made trips to manhattan which gave her a chance 
to try different kinds of clothes 
wed go every year to the nutcracker and go to the circus 
and wed also come in to have our eyes examined it was like going 
to oz wed always get dressed up when we were a little older and 
actually lived in new york it was a shock to be in jeans and just 
be comfortable 
she postponed going to college to pursue a singing career and 
was briefly married to rock guitarist cabot wade tired of life on 
the road she enrolled at william and mary college in 1970 
majoring in drama 
after graduating she starred in a number of plays for regional 
theaters including king lear uncle vanya and a 
streetcar named desire among others 
her breakthrough came in 1980 with the broadway musical 
barnum for which she earned a tony nomination as the circus 
showmans wife and gave over 300 performances in 1984 she won a 
tony for her starring role in tom stoppards the real thing 
closes film career began in 1982 with the world according to 
garp playing the freespirited mother of robin williams she was 
a sympathetic actress at first inspiring robert redford in the 
natural and mourning an old friends suicide in the big 
chill 
but in 1987 tired of warm smiles and soft tears close jumped 
at the chance to play the sexy explosive other woman of 
fatal attraction dropping 10 pounds for the role her sweet 
image evaporating into a single pot of boiled rabbit 
she considers dangerous liaisons based on the 18thcentury 
novel her favorite film admiring the marquises cunning and 
ruthlessness as she spars with the equally formidable vicomte de 
valmont john malkovich the marquise makes and breaks rules 
close notes and is controlling her image rather being controlled 
an actress born at least 200 years too soon 
i liked some of those old roles but they didnt particulary 
interest me said close who plays nice again in sarah plain 
and tall a childrens story to be aired feb 3 on cbs 
i prefer the battles between men and women and whats cliched 
and whats not its one of the great fascinations its exhausting 
emotionally but that kind of exhaustion for me is ultimately very 
cathartic exhilarating 
