british airways plc klm royal dutch airways and 
belgiums sabena world airways announced monday they are scrapping 
their plans jointly to form a regional airline with a hub in 
brussels 
the three carriers in a joint news release cited practical 
difficulties involved in implementing the original objectives a 
klm spokesman acknowledged that uncertainty over obtaining european 
community regulatory approval was a factor 
the three airlines had intended to develop their venture into a 
regional european airline using brussels zaventem airport as the 
center of a hubandspoke route network linking 75 cities 
throughout europe 
