british airways and klm 
the capital already invested is being converted into a loan for 
repayment on dec 31 1991 the airlines said british airways said 
it already had contributed 17 million pounds or 33 million 
in amsterdam klm spokesman peter wellhuner said many factors 
led to the decision in addition to high fuel costs he cited the 
uncertainty of regulatory approval 
we have had ample consultation with the european commission on 
this case and up until now we havent had any certainty of its 
approval wellhuner said 
the european commission which safeguards competition decided 
in june that the deal could hurt competition at the brussels 
airport and offered to negotiate a settlement the airlines 
refused and instead prepared legal arguments supporting the 
arrangement 
the british government cleared the deal in july finding that 
travelers would benefit from the hub the airlines wanted to create 
british airways said the decision to scrap the joint venture 
wouldnt result in any capital loss for the company 
