<TEXT>
usg corp one of the nations largest building 
products manufacturers said today it is postponing debt payments 
and selling a major subsidiary because of the declining 
construction industry 
the company said its major bank lenders have agreed to cooperate 
in the refinancing plan in the interim usg will defer payments of 
105 million in principal due today to its senior lending banks it 
also will not make interest payments on 40 million in loans from 
subordinated bondholders 
the company said it is not making these payments in order to 
strengthen its cash position so that it can pay its trade and 
operating expenses during the financial restructuring 
it said it also is seeking an equity investor 
the plan also includes the proposed sale of dap inc a producer 
of caulks and other specialty chemical products dap had annual 
sales of 186 million in 1989 with an operating profit of 12 
million 
for the first nine months of 1990 usg lost 2 million while 
sales skidded 6 percent to 16 billion from 17 billion 
the decision to begin financial restructuring now rather than 
simply seeking shortterm amendments to our bank loan covenants is 
dictated by the continuing slowdown in construction markets said 
usg chairman eugene b connolly 
