<TEXT>
usg corp said the anemic construction industry 
is forcing it to defer debt payments restructure finances and sell 
a major subsidiary 
the company one of the nations largest building products 
manufacturers said it would not make a 105 million payment on 
principal that was due monday putting it technically in default 
and subject to court action by lenders 
usg said however that major bank lenders have agreed to go 
along with the restructuring plan while it continues to make 
interest payments on the 105 million 
the company also said it will not make interest payments due 
jan 15 on 40 million worth of bonds 
spokesman matthew gonring said officials will be in contact with 
the major bondholders but he declined to say if usg has sought 
assurances that the bondholders will not file bankruptcy petitions 
against the company 
the company said in a statement that it does not intend to file 
for protection under chapter 11 of the bankruptcy code 
an outofcourt restructuring is the best solution the 
company said 
the usg announcement reflected a steep downturn in demand for 
construction of homes and commercial real estate that has gripped 
much of the country sales of new homes for example are now at 
their lowest levels since the 198182 recession with little 
improvement expected anytime soon 
usg lost 2 million during the first nine months of 1990 while 
sales skidded 6 percent to 16 billion from 17 billion 
in the past two years the company has laid off 1100 workers 
because of economic difficulties additional employees were lost in 
the sales of subsidiaries 
usg said that as part of its restructuring it will offer for 
sale dap inc a producer of caulks and other specialty hemical 
products dap had annual sales of 186 million in 1989 with an 
operating profit of 12 million 
usg said it also is seeking an investor willing to give the 
company a major infusion 
we believe there are a number of investors who might be 
interested in making an equity investment in the company gonring 
said adding that there have been talks with potential investors 
he didnt identify any 
the company said its cash position at yearend is very strong 
and that it will pay its trade and operating expenses in a timely 
manner throughout the restructuring process 
it said it is not making the loan payments in order to assure 
liquidity during restructuring which it expects to complete before 
the end of 1991 
the decision to begin financial restructuring now rather than 
simply seeking shortterm amendments to our bank loan covenants is 
dictated by the continuing slowdown in construction markets said 
usg chairman eugene b connolly 
the company has retained salomon brothers and lazard freres 
investment banking firms to help in the restructuring 
