688 per 1000 in face amount at closing monday its yield 
which falls when prices rise was 824 percent down from 830 
percent late friday 
yields for the 30year bond posted a slight gain in 1990 ending 
up about percentage point above 1989s closing figure of 797 
percent 
the federal funds rate the bank overnight loan rate and a 
closely followed indicator of the feds activities fluctuated 
throughout the day 
economists attributed the swings to the feds injection of funds 
into the banking system on thursday and monday to ease a projected 
drought in shortterm credit 
the fed seems to have bent over backwards to provide reserves 
to the banking system said douglas mcallister a bond trader for 
prudentialbache securities inc 
the rate fluctuated in a range of 6 percentage points but didnt 
skyrocket as some economists had expected it traded around 2 
percent late monday down from 7 percent late friday according to 
the telerate inc financial information service 
at the end of the year banks aggressively borrow shortterm 
funds to shore up their balance sheets a practice known as 
window dressing this sudden surge of banks shortterm 
borrowing can causes the fed funds rate to jump dramatically based 
on the simple dynamics of supply and demand 
the intense appetite for fed funds pushed the rate to 100 
percent briefly wednesday night said carol stone senior economist 
for nomura securities international inc the feds perceived target 
for the rate is 7 percent 
the wild swings didnt surprise bond analysts 
it is nothing out of the ordinary this time of year to get 
those wild gyrations said kevin flanagan money market economist 
for dean witter reynolds inc 
